Back from the lake! I was there for a week, and layed around on the beach most of the time. The second day that i was there we went to a town called Gizycko (don't strain ur self in trying to pronounce that) and there was this festival. The set up was really kewl. The idea was to make a biggest living room in Poland. So they got a huge red blow up chair (which i would have killed to be able to sit on), a huge coffee table, some kind of blow up dresser, and the stage had a border around it that made it look like a tv. That was the only good part. They had two concerts there. The first one was a guy named Sydney Polak. He was a rapper. Now imagine this. A short, curly haired, polish guy, rapping. every last one of his songs was about beer. It was quite interesting. The second concert was from a band called Perfect. They are aparently very well known, and the peak of their career was when my mom adn dad were my age. The lead singer looked like an indian/hippie but, i really liked his pants. After we got back, we scouted the town that we're staying in for a beach. It was the crappiest beach ever. First off, it was tiny, the water had rocks on the bottom (big pointy rocks) and there was a mattress type thing underwater that we were suppose to walk on. Lets just say we weren't amused. Then later on we found a nice beach that we had to trespass on other peoples property to get too, but whatever. Also, people thing America has a smoking problem? Just come here and they'll change their mind. Every other person was smoking, and thats not an exaderation (sry bout spelling) I probably got lung cancer from all the second habd smoke that i inhaled. Moving on, there were these crazy cats all over the place. One black cat crossed our path three time, the third time he jumped out of the bushes and scared us half to death. THen when we were making dinner, there was another cat sitting outside the window. It was funny cuz it hopped up when we gave it cheese. My aunt has turned into Monica (refrence to FRIENDS, Chantal will understand). Every morning, 10 am, she comes into our room and the first thing she says is start cleaning. It was so annoying. Later on we went to HItler's bunker. He has to be the biggest coward ever. He made workers add an extra 2 meters of concrete around his bunker, and he had a little air cubby that would filter clean air into a little room in case of a gas attack. Our tour giuse told us this story about when Hitler was staying in his bunker, there was a huge mosquito problem. So the soldiers decided to pour some chemical into the water, to kill the mosquito larvea. But of course the mosquitoes just flew up, weren't killed, but in turn all the frogs in the pond were posioned. That night when Hitler didn't hear the frogs that he was accustomed too, the sodliers told him what they did and he got really pissed off. He told the men that did that, that he was going to send them out to the western front as punishment the next day. So during the night, while Hitler was sleeping, all the soldiers ran around the forsets and near by lakes and caught as many frogs as they could and put them into Hitler's pond, which saved the men from going out and fighting. Back to the town. My cousins and i walked the boardwalk so many times that i managed to find a boat name "Joanna" and "Misiu". It took pictures of course. We also went a ride in a motor boat. It was fun exept for the captain, who started insulting americans, even when he knew i was from there. If America is so stupid, then why does everyone wanna go there. We must be doing something right. It's just getting me annoyed, that when I'm here I have to defend America and when i'm back home i have to defend poland. I'm sick of it. Sorry this was kinda long. But i didn't have internet for a week, what do u expect? 5 DAYS AND COUNTING TILL I COME HOME!
BORED! Wanna come home. 6 days and counting.
Found an internet cafe but my time is about to run out. I'll post more about the trip if i can get back here. 9 days till i come home!!!!!!!!!!!
